Rating: 4
Love it. This dish has become of our our regular meals. My wife doesn't care for shrimp, so for her I substitute chicken (dark meat works better), or cubed cooked ham.

Rating: 2
This was the most bland dish I have ever made-and yes the avocados get yicky after a few minutes. It was easy and do ahead but did nothing to make the shrimp "tasty"-I used top quality shrimp and felt the oil was not only to much but too bland. Perhaps some lemon infused olive oil? something- but it was a waste of excellent shrimp-yes I am a food snob

Rating: 4
This was a great make-ahead dish! Light, tasty, elegant, and a feast for the eyes.

Rating: 4
My family loved this! And it is elegant...especially if you use red onion for color. I agree with past reviews regarding the oil...I used 1/4 cup olive oil, added a dash of lemon juice, and it was just right. I served the shrimp in an avocado half, leaving the lettuce underneath as a salad. (My father-in-law picked through the serving greens to find the shrimp pieces, and my husband now wants the dressing to appear on more regular salads.)

Rating: 4
This was absolutely delicious! The only thing I changed was the oil - I used 1/2 cup olive oil instead, and it could probably stand less. I served it with mixed greens, wrapped in a warm tortilla, alongside a buttermilk potato salad. Yum!

